===Cholesky decomposition===
A Hermitian positive semidefinite matrix formula_1 can be written as formula_231 where formula_232 is lower triangular with non-negative diagonal (equivalently formula_233 where formula_234 is upper triangular); this is the Cholesky decomposition.
If formula_1 is positive definite, then the diagonal of formula_232 is positive and the Cholesky decomposition is unique. Conversely if formula_232 is lower triangular with nonnegative diagonal then formula_238 is positive semidefinite. 
The Cholesky decomposition is especially useful for efficient numerical calculations.
A closely related decomposition is the LDL decomposition, formula_239 where formula_125 is diagonal and formula_232 is lower unitriangular.

===Williamson theorem===
Any formula_242 positive definite Hermitian real matrix formula_243 can be diagonalized via symplectic (real) matrices. More precisely, Williamson&#x27;s theorem ensures the existence of symplectic formula_244 and diagonal real positive formula_245 such that formula_246.

== Other characterizations ==
